Piroska Nagy-Mohacsi, Professor, London School of Economics and Political Science, Zsolt Darvas, Senior Fellow, Bruegel, Debora Revoltella, Chief Economist, European Investment Bank and Ivailo Izvorski, Chief Economist, World Bank Group with the moderator Sasha Vakulina analysed how changes in trade and investment flows, rising energy costs and the weakening of the industrial base affect the region’s economic model. Particular emphasis was placed on the reforms needed to strengthen competitiveness and the completion of the single market agenda.